WorkItem.Description:
Hello,
 
I'm creating an AdjacencyGraph and using the AlgorithmExtensions.Roots method to try to find all of the "exit-only" nodes.  Looking through the code a bit, this seems to be what the algorithm is intended for.  However, given a graph, {A->B,B->C}, I would expect Roots to return A, and I'm getting an empty list.  If this is an API misunderstanding on my part, appoligies for the bother.  Here's the code I'm using:
 
        static void Main(string[] args)        {            AdjacencyGraph<string, Edge<string>> graph = new AdjacencyGraph<string, Edge<string>>(false);            graph.AddVertex("A");            graph.AddVertex("B");            graph.AddVertex("C");
 
            graph.AddEdge(new Edge<string>("A", "B"));            graph.AddEdge(new Edge<string>("B", "C"));
 
            var roots = graph.Roots();
 
            Console.WriteLine("Roots:");            foreach (string vertex in roots)            {                Console.WriteLine("\t" + vertex);            }            Console.WriteLine("End Roots");
 
            var topologicalSort = AlgorithmExtensions.TopologicalSort<string, Edge<string>>(graph);            Console.WriteLine("Topological (nmake) Sort Order:");            foreach(string vertex in topologicalSort)            {                Console.WriteLine("\t" + vertex);            }            Console.WriteLine("End Topological Sort");
 
            Console.WriteLine("Press any key to exit.");            Console.ReadKey();        }
 
Thanks for your time!
 
Rich
